# Trivy vulnerability ignore file
# Syntax: <CVE-ID> [expiry]  [optional comment after a space]
#
# Examples:
#   CVE-2021-44228                  # ignore forever
#   CVE-2022-22965 2025-12-31       # ignore until end of 2025
#
# Only suppress a CVE when:
#   1. You have assessed the vulnerability and confirmed it does not apply to
#      your use case (e.g. the vulnerable code path is never executed), OR
#   2. There is no fix available yet and you have a documented risk-acceptance.
#
# Never suppress a CRITICAL or HIGH CVE without a written justification.
# For IaC misconfigurations, use the equivalent AVD-ID (e.g. AVD-AWS-0001).
#
# Keep this file sorted and add a comment with the reason for each entry.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Example suppression — REMOVE THIS and add real entries as needed
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AVD-AWS-0001 2025-12-31  # Accepted risk: S3 bucket logging not required for this non-prod env
